Here’s everything about motherhood nobody really talks about cause you’re not alone in feeling all of these 💭

You’ll question yourself constantly — and still be the best for your child.

Not every moment is beautiful. some are messy, loud, and smell like poop.

Sleep is a myth once you’re a new mom, 4 hour sleep is a luxury. 

You won’t magically know what you’re doing, It’s all trial, error, tears, Google and instinct because perfection is a myth.

You’ll grieve your old self while also loving the new one. 

Tag a mom who would relate to this 🫠
